 thin slices (approx. 5 mm thickness)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"20 - 40 g butter, softened"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"60 g pure maple syrup"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"150 g pouring (whipping) cream"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"700 g milk"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tbsp raw cacao powder (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tsp natural vanilla extract"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chocolate sauce"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"120 g butter"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"150 g double cream (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g coconut sugar (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ - ½ tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g raw cacao powder (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"pouring (whipping) cream, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1921.9 kJ \/ 457.6 kcal","9.8 g","39.2 g","29.4 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["<b>Baby's serve<b>: because this pudding includes maple syrup (which is a form of sugar), you should ideally wait until your child is over 12 months before serving.","<b>Toddler's serve<b>: serve as is as an occasional treat, cut up as needed, keeping serving sizes small. Omit or reduce the chocolate sauce for a lower-sugar option.","You can replace the coconut sugar with Rapadura sugar in this recipe.","You can replace the double cream with pouring (whipping) cream in this recipe.","If you don't have raw cacao powder on hand, you can use regular cocoa powder in this recipe instead."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","10 portions"]}